body:
None of the actions that open browsers using code that looks like this:

    BrowserLauncher.getInstance().browse(url, null);

work for me, opening an empty Chrome window (w/ no URL).

```
IntelliJ IDEA 2017.3.4 (Community Edition)
Build #IC-173.4548.28, built on January 29, 2018
JRE: 1.8.0_144-b01 x86_64
JVM: Java HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM by Oracle Corporation
Mac OS X 10.13.3
```

To reproduce:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67586/36695495-5a9272c8-1af6-11e8-97a4-76b293484ebd.png)



I looked at my browser settings but found nothing odd:


![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67586/36695442-3b1d8c48-1af6-11e8-9ba3-96b83e554477.png)


cc @alexander-doroshko for any thoughts.

comment_data.body:
FWIW, IDEA-provided browser actions are failing for me too:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67586/36698425-ab665072-1afe-11e8-8975-c174ab61bdbf.png)
@pq Blind guess: do you have "Google Chrome.app" (with exactly this name) installed in your standard Applications folder?
@pq I checked on Mac and it works fine for me. What do you have as 'Default Browser' on the Web Browsers page in Preferences?
@pq I'm wondering if a recent Chrome or Mac OS update broke things? I noticed a lot of empty Chrome windows after trying to open other docs that have Chrome as the default app on Mac.

Maybe.  My default is indeed chrome and that's what my preferences are pointing too.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67586/36992872-19d44a16-2061-11e8-9d99-635f4d7a7bfd.png)

Interestingly, I can no longer reproduce this... (Though I know at least @devoncarew could at least briefly too.)

Maybe it was a transient chrome thing?

Thanks for following up @alexander-doroshko .  I'll close for now and re-open if it recurs.

title: Open Browser actions not working w/ Chrome on OS X.
